Grandma,

Tonight I will not be going to a meeting, but I will tomorrow.&nbsp; 

I ate a dinner salad with shrimp and chicken and goat cheese for dinner, but I'm still a little hungry and I'm going out to dinner with my boyfriend before a show.&nbsp; 

i really want some toast with butter, and maybe some jelly and an egg or three and a hamburger patty.&nbsp; But I'll probably settle for toast, because what I really want right now is something carby and buttery.&nbsp; I'll make it wheat.

The meeting last night had no gay men and that made me sad.&nbsp; I think more gay men should save themselves from food addiction and body self-loathing, and now!&nbsp; but that's probably because it will take the attention off of me.&nbsp; The people I'm meeting are all telling my story, male or female, gay or straight.&nbsp; I eat for 2 but exercise for 4, I hate my body, I hate my brain...but when I work through the bullshit I feel ok.&nbsp; 

It's a good feeling to know I just have to get through one more meal tonight, and that the hardest part of the day is over.

Going to work and waiting on people...preparing THEIR food and drinks and watching them slurp it down without crying or getting fat makes me want to pinch them really hard until they bleed...instead, I usually drink coffee or overeat in the back--but it's been almost a week now, and I'm dealing with it in other ways...imagining each of them imploding.

Miss you.

Love,
Sean

A guy who asked me on the first date if I'd like to move in with he and his mother in Korea town, a guy who asked if I'd pee on him, a guy who collected teddy bears, a guy with a kid and a sex addiction, and a few guys who were absolutely perfect...so perfect in fact that I couldn't stand talking to them...

4 years of serial dating, stabbing expectations in the heart after 3 weeks of dating at a time, dreams of being happily committed--buried like an episode of Dexter.

Sentence fragments that do not lend well to quality writing...

After breaking things off with an awesome guy last Spring I gave in and decided to be single...maybe even celibate.&nbsp; I wasn't asking for a guy anymore.&nbsp; I was asking for answers.&nbsp; Why was I looking so hard for a guy to make my life complete?&nbsp; I had finally stopped sleeping with people because I was lonely and bored, and I stopped overeating for the same reasons.&nbsp; I was getting it.&nbsp; I was hanging out with my friends more, and being alone more, too.&nbsp; I was so balanced and comfy walking alone to get sushi on Friday nights and going home to write, and falling asleep just before 11 PM, instead of spending the evening getting torked and blowing someone behind PinkBerry.&nbsp; I was reconnecting to the fat person in my soul in a way, the outsider that grew passionate about being non-sexual, about being alone and enjoying my space.&nbsp; I was Miss Independent...I was the Kelly Clarkson that Kelly Clarkson wants to be.

I was figuring out how to end my 20's. I discovered some of my life's purpose.&nbsp; The first time I had the nerve to say what I wanted to do with my life was to a guy I met one night after my set at the Akbar this past summer.&nbsp; I just trusted him.&nbsp; I felt like I knew him.&nbsp; 

I was funny again. I was writing more and performing more and loving that, too.

But now, I had met this guy and I'd promised myself NO MORE...no more looking for a guy to make me forget about reality so I could live with my head in the clouds, who I'd only have sex with a couple of times, anyway.

But when love takes you in, and trust me, love does takes you in--it's so hard to fight because the feeling is so euphoric...especially at first when he's not asking you to pee on him.&nbsp; "MOM, I'M IN LOVE.&nbsp; WHY?&nbsp; BECAUSE HE DOESN'T WANT TO PEE ON ME!!!"&nbsp; I met someone who I liked hanging out with more than anyone else, and we do almost every day.&nbsp; We go on Weekend Trips together with NO BREAKS FROM EACH OTHER FOR DAYS AT A TIME.&nbsp; No time for me to leave and fix my hair or think of witty topics to dazzle him with my charming yet manufactured hilarity...just me, warts and all, with him during the silent times of nothingness....&nbsp; 

It's the first time I've really felt true love.&nbsp; Can you believe it took me until 29 to find it?&nbsp; You've seen what a snack I am.&nbsp; 

I am&nbsp; so "Where the Red Fern Grows" in my attachment to him.&nbsp; Spending time together is just what we do and even after four months, it's so new to me--a person who grew up alone or with non-sexual friends as my safety shield to the outside world.&nbsp; 

He's the only person I've had sex with since the day I met him.&nbsp; Isn't that so weird?&nbsp; And it's awesome (seriously, he's a great lay).&nbsp; It feels like our bodies were designed as custom electrical sockets.&nbsp; We're a Home Depot dream accessory.&nbsp; And even when we fight, it's time we get to spend TOGETHER.&nbsp; We don't fight over right or wrong.&nbsp; We fight over understanding.&nbsp; We're the healthiest gay actor/performer son of crazy people couple I know of.&nbsp; It's scary.

It's scary.&nbsp; The fat person in me is scared because I never thought I'd ever leave sushi night (solo) for Bennigan's to share a Turkey O' Toole (add tomato).&nbsp; The gay person in me is scared because I'm not out being burned by the latest trick at the gym.&nbsp; The independent bitch in me is scared of losing myself, that I'm allowing a guy in to make my life complete and DR. PHIL SAYS THATS WRONG!...I'm scared...and that brings out the worst in me.

But he brings out the best in me.&nbsp; And that's what I was missing before that night at the Akbar.

I think it would be fun if you had sex with your partner in holiday themes.&nbsp; 

On Halloween it's lots of Candles and the Thriller album.&nbsp; Maybe you spook each other by randomly thrusting and yelling "ARGHHH!"&nbsp; Or like on Arbor day, instead of planting a tree---you skip the condoms and try for a baby.&nbsp; On Canada day you take turns being on top.&nbsp; At Easter you hide behind your stuff naked with multi-colored zig zags painted on your belly and hope they find you.&nbsp; At Christmas you put a stocking on your wiener.&nbsp; On Grandparents day you skip the Viagara and blame your impotence on your fake hip.&nbsp; on July 4 you declare your love in caligraphy notes burned at the edges, then get drunk and bang on a river dock, just before dumping boxes of Costco sized teabags into the water.

It's Halloween and no one is knocking for candy.&nbsp; Good.&nbsp; God damn I have to poo.&nbsp; And I know that as soon as I poo, the door will ring.&nbsp; I will wipe poorly, etc., etc., etc.

On New Year's Eve you hire a bunch of drunk teenagers to bang pots and pans together while you make love.&nbsp; On Martin Luther King day you just have phone sex, since only one of you will have the day off from work.&nbsp; On Pearl Harbor day you put on a lei and rape someone.&nbsp; 

WHERE ARE THESE KIDS?&nbsp; Is it because I live in an apartment?
